I remember that book. It made me think a lot about how people treat each other and how the tree just kept giving. That's a great start. Let's analyze the characterization in the story. How does Silverstein develop the characters of the boy and the tree throughout the narrative? What are their defining traits at different stages of their relationship? And how do their roles evolve? Think about the narrative arc of each character.

