00:00:57,811 --> 00:01:22,955
The boy starts off really innocent and playful, just enjoying simple things with the tree. But as he gets older, he becomes more demanding and self-centered. He only seems to come to the tree when he needs something specific, like money or a house. The tree, on the other hand, is consistently portrayed as loving and selfless. Its main purpose seems to be making the boy happy, no matter the cost to itself. It's always happy when it gives.

